  "canonical_definition": "A transformer (in machine learning) is a neural network architecture introduced by Vaswani et al. 2017 whose layers are built from multi-head self-attention and position-wise feed-forward sublayers with residual connections and layer normalization, processing all positions in a sequence in parallel rather than recurrently.",
